<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1584,2005]" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zilberman" authorityYear="2019" box="[199,466,1584,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belleae">
<emphasis box="[199,466,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">Termitozophilus belleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1901" box="[781,873,1584,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[781,873,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by integument mostly dark brown, widest region of head in basal region, clos to foramen magnum, presence of strong secondary sclerotization of tergites, long spine-like bristles and trapezoidal shape of elytra. In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1901" box="[849,941,1656,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[849,941,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very elongate antennomere XI, which is about three times longer than wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1584,2005]" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">
The absence of suture separating mentum-submentum in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zilberman" authorityYear="2019" box="[866,1137,1728,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belleae">
<emphasis box="[866,1137,1728,1753]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">Termitozophilus belleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique in the genus, a possible convergent character shared with the other Corotocini groups. Since specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mann" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1193,1328,1764,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirandus">
<emphasis box="[1193,1328,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. mirandus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not available for dissection, I propose to revise description of the genus provided in Seevers’s (1957) monograph.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1584,2005]" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">
Additional differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zilberman" authorityYear="2019" box="[559,827,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belleae">
<emphasis box="[559,827,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">Termitozophilus belleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1901" box="[883,976,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[883,976,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the position of bristle P2 on labrum, which is placed before middle of labrum length in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zilberman" authorityYear="2019" box="[756,869,1872,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belleae">
<emphasis box="[756,869,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. belleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and after the middle in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1901" box="[1162,1259,1872,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[1162,1259,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; chaetotaxy of mentum is composed of bristles 
<emphasis box="[518,546,1909,1932]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">pa</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[602,628,1909,1932]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">px</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zilberman" authorityYear="2019" box="[666,776,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belleae">
<emphasis box="[666,776,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. belleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[832,860,1909,1932]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">ap</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[875,903,1909,1932]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">pa</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[959,986,1909,1932]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">px</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1901" box="[1023,1116,1908,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[1023,1116,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; chaetotaxy of tergite IX, is composed of six bristles in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zilberman" authorityYear="2019" box="[468,579,1944,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belleae">
<emphasis box="[468,579,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. belleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. and five in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1901" box="[727,822,1944,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[727,822,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and tergite VIII is about twice wider than long in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zilberman" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belleae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. belleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and subquadrate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silvestri" authorityYear="1901" box="[464,557,1980,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[464,557,1980,2005]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">T. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="110" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="110">
In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zilberman" authorityYear="2019" box="[229,496,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Termitozophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belleae">
<emphasis box="[229,496,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="110">Termitozophilus belleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
wings were absent. The presence or absence of wings in genera of Corotocini needs to be reexamine. In genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Schiodte, 1853" authorityName="Schiodte" authorityYear="1853" box="[444,723,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Corotoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[444,549,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="110">Corotoca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schiodte, J. M. C." box="[556,723,188,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" pagination="101 - 103" refId="ref6283" refString="Schiodte, J. M. C. (1853) On some Staphylinidae, found in the nests of termites. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 21, 101 - 103." type="journal article" year="1853">Schiødte, 1853</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Corotocina), there are some species with wings developed and other with wings reduced, as discussed in a previous paper (
<bibRefCitation author="Zilberman, B." box="[845,1041,223,248]" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" pagination="547 - 560" refId="ref6516" refString="Zilberman, B. (2018) New species and synonymy in the genus Corotoca Schiodte, 1853 (Coleoptera, Aleocharinae, Corotocini). Zootaxa, 4434 (3), 547 - 560. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4434.3.9" type="journal article" year="2018">Zilberman, 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Mann, 1923" authorityName="Mann" authorityYear="1923" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Thyreoxenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1212,1354,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="110">Thyreoxenus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mann, W. M." pageId="15" pageNumber="110" pagination="323 - 366" refId="ref6173" refString="Mann, W. M. (1923) New genera and species of termitophilous Coleoptera from northern South America. Zoologica, 3 (17), 323 - 366." type="journal article" year="1923">Mann, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobson, H. R. &amp; Kistner, D. H. &amp; Pasteels, J. M." box="[221,471,260,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 245" refId="ref6071" refString="Jacobson, H. R., Kistner, D. H. &amp; Pasteels, J. M. (1986) Generic revision, phylogenetic classification, and phylogeny of the termitophilous tribe Corotocini (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Sociobiology, 12 (1), 1 - 245." type="journal article" year="1986">
Jacobson 
<emphasis box="[332,382,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="110">et al</emphasis>
. (1986)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that the wings were present, but in the original description of the genus, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mann, W. M." pageId="15" pageNumber="110" pagination="323 - 366" refId="ref6173" refString="Mann, W. M. (1923) New genera and species of termitophilous Coleoptera from northern South America. Zoologica, 3 (17), 323 - 366." type="journal article" year="1923">Mann (1923)</bibRefCitation>
observed that in 
<taxonomicName authority="Mann, 1923" authorityName="Mann" authorityYear="1923" box="[418,828,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Thyreoxenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchellus">
<emphasis box="[418,682,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="110">Thyreoxenus pulchellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mann, W. M." box="[689,828,296,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" pagination="323 - 366" refId="ref6173" refString="Mann, W. M. (1923) New genera and species of termitophilous Coleoptera from northern South America. Zoologica, 3 (17), 323 - 366." type="journal article" year="1923">Mann, 1923</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the wings were absent (confirmed here).
</paragraph>
